<p>Björk's arbitrage theory offers several benefits for practitioners and researchers in mathematical finance:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Rigorous Foundations:</strong> The theory is based on solid mathematical principles, providing a firm foundation for modeling financial markets.</li>
<li><strong>Practical Applications:</strong> The theory has numerous practical applications in pricing and risk management, making it directly relevant to industry practitioners.</li>
<li><strong>Theoretical Insight:</strong> The theory provides deeper insights into the behavior of financial markets and the fundamental principles of pricing and risk assessment.</li>
</ul>
